---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="NASA Projects & The Moon Landing — Nazaryah"
  description="NASA tells you what they worship in every project name. The most celebrated achievement in American science is named after the angel of the bottomless pit. And the church said nothing."
>
  <div class="sw-wrap">

    <!-- ── HERO ── -->
    <section class="sw-hero">
      <a href="/sun-worship/the-priesthood/nasa" class="sw-back">&#8592; The New Priesthood</a>
      <p class="sw-label">&#8213; The Priesthood / NASA &#8213;</p>
      <h1 class="sw-title">NASA Projects &amp; The Moon Landing</h1>
      <p class="sw-sub">
        Names, Images, and Contradictions That Hide in Plain Sight
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- ── INTRO ── -->
    <section class="sw-section">
      <div class="sw-prose">
        <p>
          NASA tells you what they worship in every project name. They show you what they know in every composite image. They tell you the truth in the names of their operations — and then rely on the fact that you will never look up what those names mean. This study examines the patterns that emerge when you simply read the labels on the box.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── PANTHEON ON THE LAUNCHPAD ── -->
    <section class="sw-accordion-section">
      <p class="sw-accordion-label">&#8213; A Pantheon on the Launchpad &#8213;</p>
      <h2 class="sw-accordion-title">Every Major NASA Program — Named After a Deity</h2>
      <p class="sw-accordion-sub">Not one program in the entire history of the agency has been named after anything from Scripture. Select each to examine the name.</p>

      <div class="sw-accordion">

        <details class="sw-detail">
          <summary class="sw-summary"><span class="sw-part-label">Program One</span><span class="sw-part-title">Mercury Program (1958–1963)</span><span class="sw-chevron">+</span></summary>
          <div class="sw-body">
            <p>Named after the Roman messenger god. Greek equivalent: Hermes — the very same Hermes from the Hermetic tradition, the same Hermes Trismegistus whose writings inspired Copernicus, Kepler, and Newton. The god of commerce, thieves, liars, and the guide of souls to the underworld. His staff — the caduceus — is the symbol of modern medicine.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="sw-detail">
          <summary class="sw-summary"><span class="sw-part-label">Program Two</span><span class="sw-part-title">Gemini Program (1961–1966)</span><span class="sw-chevron">+</span></summary>
          <div class="sw-body">
            <p>Named after the constellation Gemini — the Twins. In Greek mythology, these are Castor and Pollux, sons of Zeus. In Acts 28:11, Paul sailed on a ship whose figurehead bore these exact twin gods. Even in the first century, these names were recognized as pagan idols.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="sw-detail">
          <summary class="sw-summary"><span class="sw-part-label">Program Three</span><span class="sw-part-title">Apollo Program (1961–1972)</span><span class="sw-chevron">+</span></summary>
          <div class="sw-body">
            <p>This is the flagship. The program that allegedly put men on the moon was named after Apollo — the Greek sun god. But Scripture gives this name a very different identity:</p>
            <div class="sw-scripture-block">
              <p class="sw-scripture-label">&#9656; Revelation 9:11</p>
              <p>"And they had a king over them, which is the angel of the bottomless pit, whose name in the Hebrew tongue is Abaddon, but in the Greek tongue hath his name Apollyon."</p>
            </div>
            <p>Apollyon. The Destroyer. The angel of the bottomless pit. The king of the abyss. The most celebrated achievement in the history of American science is named after a being Scripture identifies as the ruler of destruction. And no one in the church said a word.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="sw-detail">
          <summary class="sw-summary"><span class="sw-part-label">Program Four</span><span class="sw-part-title">Saturn V Rocket</span><span class="sw-chevron">+</span></summary>
          <div class="sw-body">
            <p>The rocket that carried Apollo to the moon was named Saturn — the Roman god Kronos, lord of time, associated with the black cube, the hexagram, and the oldest continuous thread of pagan worship on earth. Saturn is the deity condemned in Amos 5:26 and Acts 7:43 — the star of Remphan.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="sw-detail">
          <summary class="sw-summary"><span class="sw-part-label">Program Five</span><span class="sw-part-title">Artemis Program (2017–present)</span><span class="sw-chevron">+</span></summary>
          <div class="sw-body">
            <p>NASA's current moon program is named after Artemis — the Greek goddess of the moon, twin sister of Apollo. Artemis was the deity worshipped at Ephesus — the same cult that erupted in riot when Paul preached against their idol (Acts 19:24–35). Her temple at Ephesus was one of the Seven Wonders of the Ancient World. NASA's return to the moon carries her name.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="sw-detail">
          <summary class="sw-summary"><span class="sw-part-label">Program Six</span><span class="sw-part-title">Orion Spacecraft</span><span class="sw-chevron">+</span></summary>
          <div class="sw-body">
            <p>The capsule designed to carry astronauts beyond low earth orbit is named Orion — the constellation that in Egyptian mythology represents Osiris, the god of the dead and the underworld. The ruler of the afterlife. NASA's vehicle for reaching the heavens is named after the lord of the dead.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

      </div>

      <p class="sw-accordion-footnote">
        Mercury (Hermes). Gemini (sons of Zeus). Apollo (the Destroyer). Saturn (Remphan). Artemis (the moon goddess). Orion (Osiris). This is not naming. This is dedication. These are offerings to the gods of the pantheon, announced openly, and the world applauds.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- ── THE MOON LANDING ── -->
    <section class="sw-accordion-section sw-accordion-alt">
      <p class="sw-accordion-label">&#8213; The Moon Landing &#8213;</p>
      <h2 class="sw-accordion-title">The Technology They Claim They Lost</h2>
      <p class="sw-accordion-sub">In 1969, NASA claims to have landed men on the moon. Then they stopped — and say they cannot go back.</p>

      <div class="sw-accordion">

        <details class="sw-detail">
          <summary class="sw-summary"><span class="sw-part-label">Issue One</span><span class="sw-part-title">Lost Technology</span><span class="sw-chevron">+</span></summary>
          <div class="sw-body">
            <p>In 1969, NASA claims to have landed men on the moon using less computing power than a modern pocket calculator. They did it six times between 1969 and 1972. Then they stopped. And they have never gone back.</p>
            <p>In 2017, NASA astronaut Don Pettit was asked why we haven't returned to the moon. His answer was stunning:</p>
            <div class="sw-quote-inset">
              <p>"I'd go to the moon in a nanosecond. The problem is we don't have the technology to do that anymore. We used to but we destroyed that technology and it's a painful process to build it back again."</p>
              <p class="sw-quote-attr">— Don Pettit, NASA Astronaut</p>
            </div>
            <p>The most advanced space agency on earth, with a budget of over $25 billion per year, claims to have destroyed the technology that took men to the moon. The Saturn V rocket blueprints, according to multiple NASA officials, were either lost, destroyed, or rendered unusable. The original Apollo 11 telemetry tapes — the raw data from the most important event in human exploration — were recorded over to save money on magnetic tape. These are not conspiracy claims. These are NASA's own admissions.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="sw-detail">
          <summary class="sw-summary"><span class="sw-part-label">Issue Two</span><span class="sw-part-title">The Van Allen Radiation Belts</span><span class="sw-chevron">+</span></summary>
          <div class="sw-body">
            <p>Surrounding the earth are zones of intense radiation known as the Van Allen belts, discovered in 1958 by James Van Allen using data from the Explorer 1 satellite. These belts contain trapped charged particles from the sun that would deliver lethal doses of radiation to any human being passing through them without extraordinary shielding.</p>
            <p>The Apollo spacecraft were made primarily of thin aluminum. NASA claims the astronauts passed through these belts in approximately 30 minutes each way. Modern radiation scientists have acknowledged that this passage would have exposed the crew to dangerous levels of radiation — yet no Apollo astronaut ever reported or displayed symptoms of acute radiation exposure.</p>
            <p>Consider: if Yahuah placed a firmament above the earth and set boundaries for man, then a belt of intense radiation surrounding the earth is not a random natural phenomenon. It is a barrier. A wall. A boundary that says: this far and no further.</p>
            <div class="sw-scripture-block">
              <p class="sw-scripture-label">&#9656; Job 38:11</p>
              <p>"And said, Hitherto shalt thou come, but no further: and here shall thy proud waves be stayed."</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </details>

      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── EVERY IMAGE IS DIGITAL ── -->
    <section class="sw-section sw-section-alt">
      <div class="sw-prose">
        <p class="sw-section-heading">Every Image Is Digital</p>
        <p>
          Every photograph of the earth from space that NASA has released to the public is, by their own admission, a composite — a digitally assembled image created from multiple data sources, not a single photograph taken by a camera.
        </p>
        <p>
          Robert Simmon, the NASA graphic designer who created the famous 2002 "Blue Marble" image, described his process openly:
        </p>
        <div class="sw-quote-block">
          <p>"It is photoshopped, but it has to be."</p>
          <p class="sw-quote-attr">— Robert Simmon, NASA</p>
        </div>
        <p>
          The different versions of the Blue Marble released over the years show inconsistencies in the color of the oceans, the relative size of the continents, and the cloud patterns. North America appears dramatically different in size between the 2002 and 2012 versions. These are not photographs of the same object taken from different angles. They are different digital constructions.
        </p>
        <p>
          Every image of the sun, every image of the planets, every image of distant galaxies — all of them are processed, colorized, composited, and rendered. You have never seen an actual photograph of the earth as a complete sphere from a distance. What you have seen are artists' renderings presented as reality.
        </p>
        <p>
          The question is not whether these images are beautiful. The question is whether you are willing to base your entire understanding of where you live on images that the people who made them openly acknowledge are constructed.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── PROJECTS THAT TELL THE TRUTH ── -->
    <section class="sw-accordion-section">
      <p class="sw-accordion-label">&#8213; Hidden in the Name &#8213;</p>
      <h2 class="sw-accordion-title">Projects That Tell the Truth</h2>
      <p class="sw-accordion-sub">NASA has a peculiar habit of naming projects in ways that reveal more than they intend. Select each to examine what the name actually means.</p>

      <div class="sw-accordion">

        <details class="sw-detail">
          <summary class="sw-summary"><span class="sw-part-label">Project One</span><span class="sw-part-title">Project Fishbowl (1962)</span><span class="sw-chevron">+</span></summary>
          <div class="sw-body">
            <p>A series of high-altitude nuclear tests conducted as part of the larger Operation Dominic. The tests involved detonating nuclear warheads at extreme altitudes — in some cases at the very edge of what NASA considers the boundary of space. The name "Fishbowl" is striking. If you believed the earth was enclosed under a dome — a firmament — what would you call a project designed to test its limits? A fishbowl.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="sw-detail">
          <summary class="sw-summary"><span class="sw-part-label">Project Two</span><span class="sw-part-title">Operation Dominic (1962)</span><span class="sw-chevron">+</span></summary>
          <div class="sw-body">
            <p>The parent operation of Project Fishbowl. The name "Dominic" comes from the Latin <em>Dominus</em> meaning "Lord" or "Master." Combined with the Fishbowl sub-project, you have: the Lord's Fishbowl. Or more plainly — testing the enclosure that the Creator placed over the earth.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="sw-detail">
          <summary class="sw-summary"><span class="sw-part-label">Project Three</span><span class="sw-part-title">Project Looking Glass</span><span class="sw-chevron">+</span></summary>
          <div class="sw-body">
            <p>A classified program that various whistleblowers have described as involving technology capable of viewing probable future timelines. Whether or not the technology is real, the name is revealing. "Looking Glass" — a mirror. In Scripture, the firmament is described as a molten looking glass:</p>
            <div class="sw-scripture-block">
              <p class="sw-scripture-label">&#9656; Job 37:18</p>
              <p>"Hast thou with him spread out the sky, which is strong, and as a molten looking glass?"</p>
            </div>
            <p>The sky is described as strong — solid — and like a molten looking glass. If someone named a classified project "Looking Glass," they were either extraordinarily careless or they knew exactly what the sky is.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="sw-detail">
          <summary class="sw-summary"><span class="sw-part-label">Project Four</span><span class="sw-part-title">The Truman Show (1998)</span><span class="sw-chevron">+</span></summary>
          <div class="sw-body">
            <p>Not a NASA project, but a Hollywood production that tells the story of a man who lives his entire life inside a constructed dome without knowing it. His world has artificial weather, a painted sky, and a boundary he can never cross. When Truman finally reaches the edge of his world, he touches a wall. The dome. The firmament.</p>
            <p>The film ends with Truman walking through a door in the wall and leaving the constructed reality. The character's name is Truman — <em>true man</em>. The show's creator is named Christof — <em>Christ-off</em>. The one who constructed the false reality and kept the true man trapped inside it is named after the removal of the Messiah.</p>
            <p>Hollywood has a long pattern of embedding truth in fiction. The question is not whether these are coincidences. The question is how many coincidences you need before you recognize a pattern.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── THE EDGE ── -->
    <section class="sw-section sw-section-alt">
      <div class="sw-prose">
        <p class="sw-section-heading">The Edge They Won't Let You See</p>
        <p>
          In 1959 — at the height of the Cold War, when the United States and the Soviet Union could agree on virtually nothing — twelve nations signed the Antarctic Treaty, agreeing that Antarctica would be used exclusively for peaceful scientific purposes. No military activity. No mineral mining. No independent exploration. The treaty has since been signed by 54 nations.
        </p>
        <p>
          Ask yourself: in a world where nations fight wars over oil, territory, and resources — what could possibly make every major government on earth agree to leave an entire continent untouched? What is so important about Antarctica that the most powerful nations in history have collectively agreed to keep the public out?
        </p>
        <p>
          There are no direct flights across the Antarctic continent. A flight from Sydney, Australia to Santiago, Chile — which on a globe would be a relatively short path over Antarctica — instead routes northward, often stopping in cities that add thousands of miles to the journey. Flights from South Africa to Australia do the same. Flights from South America to New Zealand frequently stop in the Middle East or North America — detours that make zero sense on a globe but perfect sense if the southern landmasses are spread around the outer rim of a circular plane.
        </p>
        <p>
          Airlines cite "safety concerns" and "lack of emergency landing sites" as the reason for avoiding Antarctica. Yet flights over the Arctic, over the Sahara, over the Pacific — all with equally limited emergency options — operate daily. The excuse does not survive scrutiny.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── THEY KNOW ── -->
    <section class="sw-section">
      <div class="sw-prose">
        <p class="sw-section-heading">They Know</p>
        <p>
          The pattern across all of these projects, names, images, and restrictions points to a single conclusion: the people running these institutions know the true nature of the earth. They know about the firmament. They know about the boundary. They know what Scripture describes.
        </p>
        <p>
          They named a project "Fishbowl." They named a project "Looking Glass" — the same phrase Scripture uses for the sky. They named their rockets after the gods of the pantheon. They detonated nuclear weapons at the edge of the atmosphere. They signed a treaty keeping every civilian away from the one place on earth that could reveal the boundary. And they produced a film about a man trapped inside a dome who doesn't know his world is constructed.
        </p>
        <p>
          They use scriptural language when it suits them. "Four corners of the earth." "Foundations." "The ends of the earth." These phrases appear in military, intelligence, and government documents. They are not using them accidentally. They are describing what they know to be true — while telling the public a completely different story.
        </p>
        <div class="sw-scripture-block">
          <p class="sw-scripture-label">&#9656; Isaiah 40:22</p>
          <p>"It is he that sitteth upon the circle of the earth, and the inhabitants thereof are as grasshoppers; that stretcheth out the heavens as a curtain, and spreadeth them out as a tent to dwell in."</p>
        </div>
        <p>
          The projects, the names, and the restrictions are not failures of secrecy. They are admissions hidden in plain sight — because they know most people will never look.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── QUOTE ── -->
    <section class="sw-footer-quote">
      <p class="sw-quote-text">"Professing themselves to be wise, they became fools, and changed the glory of the incorruptible Elohim into an image made like to corruptible man."</p>
      <p class="sw-quote-ref">— Romans 1:22–23</p>
    </section>

  </div>
</BaseLayout>

